Chris Froome has tweeted a picture of his mangled bike after being rammed off the road by a hit-and-run driver while training in southern France.The Team Sky rider, who won last year&rsquo;s Tour de France, said he had been &lsquo;rammed on purpose by an impatient driver who followed me onto the pavement&rsquo;.Froome, who lives in Monaco, told his 1.3million Twitter followers he was &lsquo;okay&rsquo; but that his bike had been &lsquo;totaled&rsquo; in the collision.Chris Froome has tweeted a picture of his mangled bike after being rammed off the road by a hit-and-run driver while training in southern The 31-year-old three-time Tour de France winner wrote: &lsquo;Just got rammed on purpose by an impatient driver who followed me onto the pavement!&ldquo;Thankfully I&rsquo;m okay. Bike totaled. Driver kept going!&rsquo;The picture was geotagged from Beausoleil in France, close to Froome&rsquo;s home in Monaco.Froome is known to be training there for this year&rsquo;s Tour de France, which takes place in July. It is understood he intends to report the incident to authorities. A spokesman for the French national police said: &ldquo;Incidents like this are investigated as a matter of course, and everything will be done to find the driver involved.&rdquo;He said such road rage attacks were disturbingly common on busy roads which cyclists share with cars and lorries.There is not thought to be any stationary CCTV of the incident, although Froome or his colleagues may have captured images, or got the number plate of the car.Last month, former Giro d&rsquo;Italia winner Michele Scarponi of the Astana team was killed when he was knocked off his bike by a van while training in Italy. Scarponi, 37, who had a wife and two children, had just been named Team Astana leader for the 2017 Giro d&rsquo;Italia following a knee injury to Fabio Aru.The veteran won the 2011 Giro after Alberto Contador was stripped of the title and claimed three stage victories in the race over the course of his career. He had only just returned home after completing the Tour of the Alps when the accident occurred on April 22. Gazzetta dello Sport said he died instantly.Astana paid tribute to a &lsquo;great champion and a special guy&rsquo;. Froome is not the first Tour de France champion to be involved in a incident with a motorist while out cycling.In 2012, Britain&rsquo;s only other winner Bradley Wiggins - who was victorious that year - was knocked off his bike by a van driver.Froome (pictured with his wife and son) is known to be training there for this year&rsquo;s Tour de France, which takes place in July.